pageContext.description: MANUFACTURE:  intact top sur. of gale support tongue is rough, not like det. sur. - may be remnant of break at stump of jet; some dimpling of p. surfaces poss. moulding marks;  irregular facetting & bonks [?} on int. face of gale support prob. post-cast working, as also scattered prooks. on rev. of mould;  a sense of finer str. also took anc., CONDITION:  top and much of edges badly chipped, whole line of britten {} end lost  -  broken sur.s to pale don {} green and purply brown;  grmks along matrix, incl through attached material - no evid. that recent - could be anc., ATTACHED MATERIAL:  free patches of white-grey thin coat on matrix, almost certainly remnants of Pb eg.;  obstructed. fawn soil mainly in matrix & partly mixed with Pb traces,
